<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start by placing your hands on the floor with your upper arms parallel to your torso.</li>



<li>Rotate your hands out, with fingers pointing away from your body.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Lower yourself slowly and push back up, engaging your tricep muscles.</li>



<li>Repeat the number of reps recommended in the table below based on individual goals.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged as you go down and on the way up.</li>



<li>Keep the upper arms close to your body and elbows pointing down.</li>



<li>Breathe in as you lower and breathe out as you push up.</li>
</ul>



